# Auction CLI

Auction CLI is a command-line interface application developed to manage auction items. It allows users to add, update, remove, and list auction items in a MongoDB database via a straightforward command-line interface.

## Features

- **Add Auction Items**: Interactively add new items to the auction.
- **Update Auction Items**: Update existing items by specifying their ID.
- **Remove Auction Items**: Remove items by their ID with confirmation.
- **Find Auction Items**: Search for an item by its title.
- **List All Auction Items**: Display all auction items stored in the database.

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have met the following requirements:
- Node.js installed on your machine
- MongoDB running locally or remotely with access details
- Git (optional) for version control

## Installation

Follow these steps to get your development environment set up:

1. **Clone the repository** (if using Git):
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/auction-cli.git
   cd auction-cli

2. **Install dependencies**

npm install

## Usage
```bash
./commands.js add

./commands.js update <id>

./commands.js remove <id>

./commands.js list

./commands.js find <title>


